CHAPTER 45 1
CHAPTER 45
( HB 527 )
AN ACT relating to insurance regulatory requirements and declaring an emergency.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
Section 1. KRS 304.1-050 is amended to read as follows:
As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
(1) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of the Department of Insurance of this state; and[.]
(2) "Department" means the Department of Insurance of this state[, unless context otherwise requires].
Section 2. KRS 304.1-110 is amended to read as follows:
As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
(1) [A ]"Certificate of authority" means a certificate[is one] issued by the commissioner evidencing the authority
of an insurer to transact insurance in this state; and[.]
(2) [A ]"License" means a license or other authorization[is authority] granted by the commissioner pursuant to
this chapter that authorizes[code authorizing] the licensee to engage in a business or operation of insurance in
this state other than as an insurer[, and the certificate by which such authority is evidenced].
Section 3. KRS 304.2-160 is amended to read as follows:
(1) As used in this section, "licensee" means an individual or entity that holds a license issued by the
commissioner or department.
(2) Each written and signed complaint received by the department[ of Insurance] shall be recorded by the
department, including the subsequent disposition thereof, and maintained for a period of not less than five (5)
years.
(3) The records of[ such] complaints received by the department shall be indexed whenever applicable both by the
name of the insurer and by the name of the licensee[, including agent, surplus lines broker, adjuster,
administrator, reinsurance intermediary broker or manager, rental vehicle agent or managing employee,
specialty credit producer or managing employee, life settlement broker or provider, or consultant] involved.
(4) The commissioner shall consider[ such] complaints received by the department before issuing or renewing any
certificate of authority or license.
Section 4. KRS 304.2-220 is amended to read as follows:
For the purpose of ascertaining compliance with law, or relationships and transactions between any person and any
insurer or proposed insurer, the commissioner may as often as reasonably necessary examine the accounts, records,
documents, and transactions pertaining to or affecting the insurance affairs or proposed insurance affairs and
transactions of any:
(1) [Any ]Insurance holding company;[ or ]
(2) Person holding the shares of voting stock or policyholder proxies of an insurer as voting trustee or otherwise,
for the purpose of controlling the management thereof;
(3)[(2)] [Any ]Insurance agent, managing general agent, surplus lines broker, adjuster, consultant,
administrator, reinsurance intermediary broker or manager, rental vehicle agent,[ or] rental vehicle agent
managing employee, pharmacy benefit manager, portable electronics retailer[specialty credit producer or
managing employee], or any person holding himself or herself out as any of the foregoing;
(4)[(3)] [Any ]Person having a contract under which he or she enjoys by terms or in fact the exclusive or
dominant right to manage or control an[the] insurer, as voting trustee[,] or otherwise; and
(5)[(4)] [Any ]Person in this state engaged in,[ or] proposing to be engaged in[ this state in],[ or] holding
himself or herself out[ in this state] as so engaging or proposing, or[ in this state] assisting in the promotion,
formation, or financing of:
