(8) Nothing in this section shall be construed to create an entitlement for property owners, SKH
approved[building] contractors, or nonprofit organizations to obtain funds for, or obligate the state in any way
to fund, or maintain funding for, any activity for which a financial grant is permitted or provided under this
section.
Section 6. KRS 304.4-040 is amended to read as follows:
(1) As used in this section, "licensee" means an individual or entity that holds a license issued by the
commissioner or department.
(2) The commissioner may revoke the certificate of authority of any insurer which fails to pay when due any
taxes, fees, licenses, and other charges owing to this state. The commissioner may likewise revoke the license
of any licensee[agent, surplus lines broker, adjuster, administrator, reinsurance intermediary broker or
manager, rental vehicle agent or managing employee, specialty credit producer or managing employee, life
settlement broker or provider, or consultant,] as to whom any tax or fee required under this chapter[code] has
not been paid when due.
Section 7. KRS 304.5-080 is amended to read as follows:
