of this chapter.
Section 34. Whereas the availability of certified and approved building contractors is crucial to ensuring
that Kentucky homes are mitigated to resist future losses due to catastrophic wind and hail events, an emergency is
declared to exist, and Section 5 of this Act takes effect upon its passage and approval by the Governor or upon its
otherwise becoming a law.
Signed by Governor April 7, 2026.
